<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>As said in the title, OS-Prober doesn&#39;t detect other Distros and Windows without ntfs-3g installed, and even then it just detects them and doesn&#39;t write an entry to grub.cfg.</p> <p>My other distro is is Gentoo, where I have no problems detecting all my OSes, but os-prober takes minutes there so I&#39;d like to use Archs grub menu instead.</p> <p>The Kernel is compiled without <code>CONFIG_NTFS_FS</code> but with <code>CONFIG_NTFS3_FS</code> set, maybe that matters.</p> <p>And that doesn&#39;t explain why Gentoo on ext4 is not visible.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Zacki_404"> /u/Zacki_404 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w2uf15/osprober_doesnt_work_without_ntfs3g/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w2uf15/osprober_doesnt_work_without_ntfs3g/">[comments]</a></span>